    "body": "Alright, I found the solution. I add it here for others as a reference.\r\n\r\nPodman can use vfs or overlayfs for storage.\r\nOverlayfs seems to cause the issue.\r\n# Check current driver:\r\n```\r\npodman info | grep graph\r\n  graphDriverName: overlay\r\n```\r\n# Uninstall fuse-overlayfs\r\n# Edit /etc/containers/storage.conf:\r\n```\r\n# Default Storage Driver, Must be set for proper operation.\r\ndriver = \"vfs\"\r\n```\r\n# Delete temporary data:\r\n```\r\nrm -rf ~/.local/share/containers/*\r\n```\r\n# Now it should work. No need to use `--mount`.\r\nYou can double-check the graphql driver:\r\n```\r\npodman info | grep graph\r\n  graphDriverName: vfs\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere may be some similar differences in docker as well.",
